    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok thanks, that makes me feel better. i've actually got some old antibiotic drops from a previous prescription in my cabinet from a year ago, i think they were called tobramycin? would it be okay if i just use those instead of the lubricating drops to kill whatever is causing the gunk? it seems way faster than just waiting for the redness to go down with the warm compress.",
